(a well-placed
arrow)
Hope it was worth it.
This hangs. He turns to go.
RESNICK (CONT’D)
Ale House later. You're buying.
He leaves. Faith sits, weighed down by the burden of her
conscience.
117 EXT. KEMP HOUSE - ESTABLISHING - AFTERNOON 117
Drop down from a cloudless, vibrant Autumn sky onto Justin
and Allison's home.
118 INT. KEMP HOUSE - LIVING ROOM - AFTERNOON 118
The sound of the front door closing precedes Justin entering
the living room where Allison and the Baby lie on a blanket.
JUSTIN
And the 4Runner is officially sold.
He holds up a CHECK. Allison smiles, motions to him.
ALLISON
Get over here. We just started.
JUSTIN
Yes, Ma'am. I love me some "tummy￾time."
